    <title>Create an
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160518T101541+0200" comment="For SME: Who creats the original org unit hierarchy? Admin? Implmenter?" flag="done"?>organisation
        unit<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
    <screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata width="80%" align="center"
                    fileref="resources/images/orgunits/create_new_orgunit.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
    </screenshot>
    <para>You add organisation units to the hierarchy one by one, either as a
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160518T102014+0200" comment="For SME: Can you crate a new root? 
Follow-up with SME before release.
- 2.24. you can only have one root unit." flag="done"?>root
        unit<?oxy_comment_end?> or as a child of a selected organisation unit. You can only have one
        root unit.</para>
    <para>To create a new organisation unit:</para>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Maintenance</emphasis> app and click <emphasis
                    role="bold">Organisation units</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold">Organisation
                    unit</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the left-hand organisation unit tree, select the organisation unit you want to
                add the new organisation unit to. The selected organisation unit is marked in
                yellow.</para>
            <para>You can locate an organisation unit in the tree by expanding the branches (click
                on the arrow symbol), or by searching for it by name or code.</para>
            <note>
                <para>The search is case-insensitive for organisation unit names. For codes you need
                    to type the exact code.</para>
            </note>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Click the add button.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis> field, define the precise name of the
                organisation unit.</para>
            <para>Each organisation unit must have an unique name.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Short name</emphasis> field, define a short name for
                the organisation unit.</para>
            <para>Typically, the short name is an abbreviation of the full organisation unit name.
                This attribute is often used in reports to display the name of the organisation
                unit, where space is limited.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) In the <emphasis role="bold">Code</emphasis> field, assign a
                code.</para>
            <para>In many countries organisation units are assigned a code.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Description</emphasis> field, type a description of
                the organisation unit.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Select an <emphasis role="bold">Opening date</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>The opening dates control which organisation units that where existing at a point
                in time, for example when analysing historical data. This attribute is
                mandatory.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>If applicable, select a <emphasis role="bold">Closed date</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Comment</emphasis> field, enter any additional
                information that you would like to add.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) In the <emphasis role="bold">URL</emphasis> field, enter a link to an
                external web site that has additional information about the organisation
                unit.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Enter contact information:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Contact person</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Address</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>E-mail</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Phone number</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
            <para>This information can be vital for facilitating follow-up.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>If applicable, enter custom attributes values, for example <emphasis role="bold"
                    >HR identifier</emphasis>.</para>
            <para>You set custom attributes in <emphasis role="bold">Data administration</emphasis>
                > <emphasis role="bold">Attribute</emphasis>.
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160518T114951+0200" comment="At next revsision, add x-ref here." flag="done"?>For
                more information about how to use attributes, refer to the &quot;Attributes&quot;
                section.<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
        </listitem>
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160524T121553+0200" comment="Will be added, see Iissue on GitHub
https://github.com/dhis2/maintenance-app/issues/162
- If release on Monday, field included."?>
        <listitem>
            <para>(Optional) Enter
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160923T102103+0200" comment="For SME: are coordinates always here, or a custom attribute?"?>coordinates<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <?oxy_comment_end?>
        <listitem>
            <para><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160923T101928+0200" comment="Removed step 14 &quot;Enter Coordinates&quot;. See GitHub issue #162. SME confirms this will not be implemented for 2.25. 
Removed text:
&quot;This field is used to create the maps in the GIS module. Paste in the coordinates of the organisation unit in this field, either a polygon (for organisation units that represent an administrative boundary) or a point (for health facilities). Without this information the GIS module will not work. It might be more efficient to import these coordinates later as a batch job for all organisation units using the import module. See the GIS chapter for more details.&quot;"?>Click<?oxy_comment_end?>
                <emphasis role="bold">Save</emphasis>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
</section>
